We recommended that Management:

require the concerned accountable officers to settle/liquidate their outstanding cash advances, otherwise, enforce the withholding of salary, in accordance with Section 5.1.3 of COA C. No. 97-002; 

stop the grant of additional cash advances to personnel with unliquidated cash advances until such time previous cash advances are fully settled; 


direct the Municipal Accountant to investigate the reason for the abnormal/negative balances, and draw the necessary adjusting entry, if warranted; and 

monitor and establish controls to ensure timely liquidation of cash advances such as requiring complete documentary requirements not only upon liquidation, but even upon the granting thereof to establish accountability.

We recommended that Management:

create Inventory Committee composed of regular employees who shall work full time in the conduct of physical inventory of PPE and prepare the RPCPPE;

assign one personnel each from GSO and Accounting Office to conduct reconciliation of records with the inventory report on a full-time basis;

Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary journal entries to correct the improper derecognition of PPEs; and

Municipal Accountant to conduct one-time cleansing of PPEs in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006.

direct the reconciliation of the inventory report with accounting records; 

require the disposal of unserviceable properties;

oblige the designated GSO to prepare and maintain property cards and renew the PARE every three years; and  


instruct the Municipal Accountant to record the PPEs to their appropriate PPE accounts and semi-expendable supplies and materials to their appropriate expense accounts.
